; The "credit_card" payment method implies a specific type of transaction but does not specify the vendor (e.g., Visa, Mastercard); 
; A ride is considered "completed" if it has reached its destination without being cancelled; 
; The pickup zone and borough information can help in understanding the geographic distribution of such rides and fares.

The query assumes that a 'specific driver' refers to driver_id = 1; 
A ride 'cost more than 50' means the total_fare is greater than 50; 
The 'average fare amount' is the mean of the fare amounts for the rides.

- Manhattan refers to one of the five boroughs of New York City; 
- Average fare refers to the total fare earned by a driver divided by the number of rides; 
- Total tips refer to the sum of tips received by a driver from all completed rides.

- The top 10 drivers are determined by their total rides and total fares in descending order, with the highest values ranked first; 
- A higher ranking indicates better performance; 
- The performance metrics provide insights into the drivers' productivity and earnings; 
- The zone and borough information helps analyze the drivers' performance in different areas.
